As ‘scribere' signifies to make an entry, ‘rescribere’ signifies to cancel the entry, which would be done when the debt was paid and not before. ‘Quod tu nun- quam rescribere possis ' therefore means ‘ what you can never reoover.' ‘ Dictare ’ is to dictate the form of bond for the bor- rower to write out or the sum to be entered in his own books, and either way is equi- valent to lending money.
